### ğŸ¯ é¡¹ç›®ç›®æ ‡ | Objective  
æœ¬é¡¹ç›®æ—¨åœ¨æ„å»ºä¸€ä¸ªè½»é‡ã€éšç§ä¿æŠ¤çš„åƒåœ¾é‚®ä»¶åˆ†ç±»ç³»ç»Ÿã€‚é€šè¿‡è¯é¢‘å‘é‡æ›¿ä»£åŸå§‹æ–‡æœ¬ï¼Œå®ç°æœ¬åœ°åŒ–ç‰¹å¾æå–ä¸é™ç»´å¤„ç†ï¼Œè¿›ä¸€æ­¥æ¯”è¾ƒå¤šç§åˆ†ç±»æ¨¡å‹ï¼ˆRandom Forest ä¸ RBF-SVMï¼‰åœ¨ä¸åŒé¢„å¤„ç†ä¸‹çš„è¡¨ç°ï¼Œæœ€ç»ˆå®ç°é«˜æ•ˆçš„é‚®ä»¶è¯†åˆ«ã€‚  
This project aims to build a lightweight, privacy-preserving spam email classification system. By replacing raw text with word frequency vectors and applying local dimensionality reduction (e.g., PCA), we evaluate the performance of models like Random Forest and RBF-SVM under different preprocessing pipelines for accurate and secure classification.

---

### ğŸ”§ æŠ€æœ¯å·¥å…· | Technologies  
- Python, scikit-learn, NumPy, Pandas  
- Natural Language Processing (Word Frequency Vector)  
- Random Forest, RBF Support Vector Machine (SVM)  
- Principal Component Analysis (PCA), SMOTE  
- Data Visualization with Seaborn & Matplotlib

---

